::{{DIcon|Talk}} Tell me about your ghostwriting.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501024250-->
:::'''Amo:''' Have you heard of ''Tale of the Winterlands'', the fiction that was recently banned? The publisher was actually quite happy with the quality and wanted the author to make some edits on the original so that they can publish it again.
:::'''Amo:''' But they did not expect the author to simply vanish into thin air! The editors had to contact me instead, asking if I can help with the project.
:::'''Amo:''' "Ha! Tale of the Winterlands is just some cheap folklore compiled together. I can give you one hundred thousand to two hundred thousand words with ease. Piece of carrot cake to me." &mdash; That was my response when I took the job. You know how hard it is to finally get something going. I was just trying to impress them but ended up getting way ahead of myself.
:::'''Amo:''' One of the editors had sent me a copy to let me get the feel of it. It wasn't until I started reading that I realized the book was going to be a classic. I had to admit, I couldn't even remotely reproduce the author's creativity and style.
:::'''Amo:''' The editor has made several attempts to contact me since then, but I managed to avoid her each time because I just couldn't deliver.
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_5010242_21-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_5010242_21-->
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} How would you rate ''Tale of the Winterlands'' now?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501024256-->
::::'''Amo:''' A Masterpiece of a true genius. Maybe the language still has room for polishing, but the wild passion weaved into the plot is other-worldly. For seven hundred years the people of Belobog have been trapped in the snow, their imagination taken away. This book reignited people's desire to look beyond these snow-covered lands...
::::'''Amo:''' Maybe that's why the Architects insist on banning it... I heard that within a month of the book's publication, the number of people that ventured out into the snow and went missing had gone up exponentially.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} What's your plan for the future?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501024259-->
::::'''Amo:''' To avoid the editors for the time being.
::::'''Amo:''' And contemplate on what to do for a living if I'm blocklisted... *sigh*
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} Don't put so much pressure on yourself.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501024262-->
:::'''Amo:''' Sorry, I've had a difficult time lately...
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_5010242_31-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_5010242_31-->
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Don't give up just yet. Pull yourself up by your bootstraps.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501024264-->
::::'''Amo:''' Hehe, easier said than done.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Stop comparing yourself to others. Go with your instincts!
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501024266-->
::::'''Amo:''' Hah! I'll become a laughingstock in the history of literature if I do that. "Who's this Amo? How dare he write this rubbish and claim to be writing ''Tale of the Winterlands''?"
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} No need to stick to one career path. How about doing something else?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501024268-->
