:{{DIcon|undefined}} I hear you need help.
::<!--Trigger PerformanceE 301042101: Config/Level/Mission/3010421/Act/Act301042101.json-->
::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_301042102-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_301042102-->
::'''Amo:''' Did you? You know, I often come here to contemplate life. When I am looking at that trashcan, I feel like I am looking at myself. I'm close to 30 but I haven't achieved anything in life.
::'''Amo:''' A few days ago, I came here like I always do, and I found a beautiful postcard lying in the trashcan. Surprisingly, it was addressed to me, it was from "Garbage King."
::'''Amo:''' I've heard things about this "Garbage King." They say he's a mysterious scavenger and nobody knows who he really is. Maybe I've been hanging around this trashcan for so long that I caught his attention.
::'''Amo:''' At first, I thought I trespassed somebody's territory and this was a warning... Unexpectedly, the postcard is full of encouragement. He said he's read my novel and he really loves my stories. He told me not to give up. It was really...
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_301042101_12-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_301042101_12-->
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Touching...
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Suspicious...
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_301042108-->
::'''Amo:''' No... devastating!
::'''Amo:''' Maybe he's just trying to cheer me up. But from his words, I see a writer much more talented than myself.
::'''Amo:''' Look &mdash; "The birth of a person is like rubbish landing in the trashcan. There's a pleasant sound and it brings joy to people." What a wonderful metaphor. It's like I am reading about wars in the distant past...
::'''Amo:''' And this &mdash; "My friend, we have a long life ahead of us and you still have time to experience your life, until Belobog sends off the last trashcan." How much sorrow does one have to endure before one can write such romantic prose?
::'''Amo:''' Words that take me ages to come up with seem so easy to him. I feel like... I am conversing with a "King" who conquered the wind and snow. Like he is a saint while I am just an insignificant vagrant!
::'''Amo:''' Now I can't focus on anything else. If you know anything about this "Garbage King," please let me know.
::'''Amo:''' I want to know who he is, where he comes from and what he has been through. At least I want to understand the gap between us...
::<!--Custom String Trigger: ALL_TALK_END-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: ALL_TALK_END-->
::<!--Ends the current performance-->
